25|$|Due to {{historical}} reasons {{and the political}} nature of its work, <b>the</b> <b>IAEA</b> is not a specialized agency. Instead, {{its relationship to the}} United Nations is governed by a special agreement as well as by its statute that commits <b>the</b> <b>IAEA</b> to report annually to the General Assembly and, when appropriate, to the Security Council.|$|E
25|$|In December 1991, the Quadripartite Agreement was {{established}} among Brazil, Argentina, the ABACC and <b>the</b> <b>IAEA.</b> It regulated IAEA inspections in Brazil and Argentina, while recognizing the SCCC and stating {{the need to}} avoid duplication of work between ABACC and <b>the</b> <b>IAEA.</b> The accord came into force in 1994 {{and it has been}} in force since then.|$|E
